This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it proposes a new linguistic stegosystem based on a Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) neural network. It also uses Twitter and Enron email datasets, which are commonly used in natural language processing research. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as the paper is motivated by concerns for user privacy and proposes a steganographic system to enable encrypted message exchange without detection by adversaries. 

The paper's use of LSTM neural networks suggests it could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). 

Finally, the paper's focus on user privacy and security could also place it in the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
